Key files and purposes:

  Entry:
  - run_game.py:1 — CLI launcher; adds path and calls main()
  - snake_game/main.py:8 — Creates Settings + SnakeGameServer, starts Flask on port 5000

  Config:
  - snake_game/config/settings.py:7 — Settings: port, grid (20×20), canvas (600×600), neon color palette

  Server:
  - snake_game/server/web_server.py:8 — SnakeGameServer: Flask app, serves / (index.html) and /api/colors; mounts static/templates
  
  Core Logic (snake_game/core/):
  - snake_game.py:9 — Point: 2D coordinate with equality/hash
  - snake_game.py:22 — Snake: body list, direction, move(), change_direction() (blocks reverses), grow(), check_collision()
  - snake_game.py:79 — Food: random generation avoiding snake body
  - snake_game.py:105 — SnakeGame: orchestrates state, score, bonus food spawning (every 5 foods), power-up integration, get_game_state()
  - power_ups.py:10 — PowerUp: tracks type, duration/count, expiration
  - power_ups.py:49 — PowerUpManager: activates effects (magnet, ghost, mirror, shield, speed, points), handles mirror snake, teleport/bomb
  - bonus_food.py — Bonus food types (lightning, bomb, magnet, freeze, rainbow, mirror, shield, ghost)

  Frontend:
  - templates/index.html:1 — Canvas + UI, injects colors, loads game.js + helpers
  - static/js/game.js:1 — SnakeGame class: full client-side game loop (setInterval), input, collisions, draw, power-up effects, particles; persists high score in localStorage
